column35: Raw sequencing reads were trimmed for adaptor sequences. For RNA-Seq, clipped reads were aligned to human genome (hg19)  using STAR. For ATAC-Seq, clipped reads were mapped to human genome (hg19) using Bowtie2 (v2.3.3.1) with the parameters
column36: Reads of RNAseq were counted by featureCounts with paraments

column12: All cells were cultured in RPMI 1640 medium supplemented with 10% fetal calf serum (FCS) and 1% Penicillin-Streptomycin at 37°C incubator with 5% CO2.
column14: MACS2 (v2.1.1.20160309) was used for peak-calling ., BigWig files of ATAC-Seq was generated by deeptools (v3.3.0).
column43: 1 ug of total RNA from each sample were used for RNA-seq library preparation according manufacturer's instructions of NEBNext Ultra Directional RNA Library Prep Kit (NEB). ATAC-seq: ATAC-seq library processing was performed following the Omni-ATAC protocol (M Ryan Corces et al. 2017), and Vazyme Tn5 transposase (TD501) was used for transposition.
